'''2020年7月日本水災'''（{{lang-ja|令和２年７月豪雨}}）是發生於2020年7月[[日本|日本]]廣泛地區因[[暴雨|暴雨]]造成的[[水災|水災]]、[[泥石流|泥石流]]。

此水灾已造成至少78人死亡、4人失蹤<ref name="fdma"/><ref name=Reuters7>{{cite news |title=Japan boosts rescue efforts as it warns of more rain in flood-hit areas |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-japan-floods/japan-boosts-rescue-efforts-as-it-warns-of-more-rain-in-flood-hit-areas-idUSKBN2480CH |agency=Reuters |date=2020-07-07 |accessdate=2020-07-08 |archive-date=2020-07-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708054107/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-japan-floods/japan-boosts-rescue-efforts-as-it-warns-of-more-rain-in-flood-hit-areas-idUSKBN2480CH |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nishinippon.co.jp/item/n/623967/|title=熊本豪雨の死者52人に　行方不明10人、8万人態勢で捜索|publisher=[[西日本新聞|西日本新聞]]|date=2020-07-08|accessdate=2020-07-08|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707230004/https://www.nishinippon.co.jp/item/n/623967/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在受災最嚴重的[[熊本縣|熊本縣]]，一間老人院被水淹沒，造成14人心肺停止（後均確認罹難）<ref name=BBCJuly4>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-53290211|title=Many feared dead in flooded Japanese care home|date=2020-07-04|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=2020-07-07|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707133552/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-53290211|dead-url=no}}</ref>。熊本縣內共9條河川嚴重泛濫，其中[[球磨川|球磨川]]流域內的[[球磨村|球磨村]]、[[人吉市|人吉市]]等多個市町村落的道路中斷<ref>{{cite news|title=九州豪雨「第5級黑色警戒」：日本梅雨水災擴散，熊本最慘已51死|url=https://global.udn.com/global_vision/story/8662/4683658|newspaper=聯合新聞網|date=2020-07-07|accessdate=2020-07-07|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707155612/https://global.udn.com/global_vision/story/8662/4683658|dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[球磨川|球磨川]]有11处河岸被淹没、1处[[決堤|決堤]]。<ref name=kyodonews2/>

== 背景 ==
连年来，日本遭受台风、雷暴和大洪水重创。除[[北海道|北海道]]，日本全境处在初夏[[梅雨|梅雨]]时节。日本多山的地形酝酿了洪水和泥石流的风险。过去几年的气象灾害已造成数百人遇难，气象专家表示[[全球变暖|全球变暖]]是灾害的成因之一<ref name=NYTimes>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/04/world/asia/japan-rains-flooding-landslides.html|title=Severe Flooding in Southern Japan Swamps Nursing Home|first=Gerry|last=Mullany|date=2020-07-04|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2020-07-10|archive-date=2020-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706023202/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/04/world/asia/japan-rains-flooding-landslides.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[球磨川|球磨川]]盆地的上一次洪灾是在1965年。作为日本三大洪流之一，球磨川是长达{{convert|115|km|mi}}的[[一级水系|一级水系]]，源头位于[[熊本縣|熊本縣]]南部山区，流经[[人吉市|人吉市]]、[[球磨村|球磨村]]和[[八代市|八代市]]，最终汇入[[八代海|八代海]]<ref name=TJN>{{cite web|url=https://the-japan-news.com/news/article/0006653387|title=Kuma River floods cities after record rainfall|work=The Japan News|accessdate=2020-07-04|archive-date=2020-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200704202137/https://the-japan-news.com/news/article/0006653387|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 灾情 ==
[[File:令和2年（2020年）7月3日からの大雨・斜め写真・球磨川地区（熊本県八代市、芦北町、球磨村）124A2490.jpg|left]]淹没的房屋]]
2020年7月3日晚上开始，受暖湿气流进入低气压和[[梅雨|梅雨前线]]的影响，[[鹿儿岛县|鹿儿岛县]]的[[萨摩|萨摩]]和[[大隅|大隅]]3日晚至4日早晨、[[熊本县|熊本县]]南部从4日凌晨到早上、局部地区下起了猛烈的雨。<ref>{{Cite web|title=熊本県と鹿児島県に大雨特別警報 気象庁、最大級の警戒求める|url=https://www.sankei.com/affairs/news/200704/afr2007040001-n1.html|website=産経ニュース|date=2020-07-04|accessdate=2020-07-08|language=ja|first=SANKEI DIGITAL|last=INC|archive-date=2020-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200705081158/https://www.sankei.com/affairs/news/200704/afr2007040001-n1.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2020年7月4日日本南部[[九州岛|九州岛]]连串强降雨引发洪水。当地时间凌晨4:50，[[日本气象厅|日本气象厅]]将九州部分地区的强降雨警戒级别提升至最高的第三级——[[特别警报|特别警报]]<ref name="0705fukuoka">[https://www.jma-net.go.jp/fukuoka/chosa/saigai/20200705_fukuoka.pdf 災害時気象資料：令和2年7月3日から4日にかけての熊本県・鹿児島県の大雨について] {{Wayback|url=https://www.jma-net.go.jp/fukuoka/chosa/saigai/20200705_fukuoka.pdf |date=20200711091618 }}福岡管区気象台、2020年7月5日。</ref>，属史上首次<ref name=kyodonews/>，这些地区可能出现了由发达的雨云相连的{{link-en|线状降水带|Training (meteorology)}}<ref>{{Cite web|title=気象庁「線状降水帯が発生の可能性」 九州南部の大雨特別警報|url=https://www.sankei.com/life/news/200704/lif2007040004-n1.html|website=産経ニュース|date=2020-07-04|accessdate=2020-07-08|language=ja|first=SANKEI DIGITAL|last=INC|archive-date=2020-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708232319/https://www.sankei.com/life/news/200704/lif2007040004-n1.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。气象厅表示，当地的降雨量强所未见<ref name= BBCJuly4/>，每小时超过{{convert|100|mm|in|sp=us}}<ref name=AP>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/9db72f673863802bddbbc1799450fafd|title=Japan floods leave up to 34 dead, many at nursing homes|date=2020-07-05|website=AP News|accessdate=2020-07-06|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707133556/https://apnews.com/9db72f673863802bddbbc1799450fafd|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2020年7月5日傍晚到6日上午，鹿儿岛县的萨摩和大隅地方局部地区下了猛烈的雨，[[鹿屋市|鹿屋市]]等地下了创纪录的大雨。<ref name="0708kagoshima">[https://www.jma-net.go.jp/fukuoka/chosa/saigai/20200708_kagoshima.pdf 災害時気象資料：令和2年7月5日から6日にかけての鹿児島県の大雨について] {{Wayback|url=https://www.jma-net.go.jp/fukuoka/chosa/saigai/20200708_kagoshima.pdf |date=20200711083503 }}鹿児島地方気象台、2020年7月8日。</ref>。

2020年7月9日，官方确认水灾共造成60人死亡，约12人失踪<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kyodo|first=Jiji|date=2020-07-09|title=Rescuers battle to reach thousands trapped by floods in Kyushu|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/07/09/national/kyushu-floods-rescue/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200709032032/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/07/09/national/kyushu-floods-rescue/|archive-date=2020-07-09|access-date=2020-07-09|website=The Japan Times|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[共同通讯社|共同通讯社]]报道指，当地共发生12次[[山崩|山崩]]，130万名紧急撤离<ref name=Reuters7/>。

熊本县球磨村一家养老院被洪水淹没，14名居民死亡<ref name=kyodonews/><ref name= BBCJuly4/>[[熊本縣知事列表|熊本县知事]][[蒲岛郁夫|蒲岛郁夫]]表示洪水和[[泥石流|泥石流]]涌入养老院，冲散了数十人<ref name=NYTimes />。一名搜救志愿者表示，他们抵达现场时，水位还在一楼。救援人员尝试营救上到二楼的居民，但无法救出楼下的居民<ref name=AP/>。养老院一名职员表示，他们凌晨5点叫醒大家，将他们拖上楼。水涌入一楼的时候，他们将坐轮椅的老人放在了餐厅的桌子上。之后水冲破窗户涌入，老人们浮了起来，职员无法救出罹难的老人<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://weather.com/news/news/2020-07-06-japan-flooding-kumamoto-kyushu-forecast-evacuations|title=Japan Warns of More Flooding as Toll Reaches at Least 44; Several Others Missing|website=The Weather Channel|accessdate=2020-07-10|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707133601/https://weather.com/news/news/2020-07-06-japan-flooding-kumamoto-kyushu-forecast-evacuations|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first=Takuya|last=Arakaki|url=http://www.asahi.com/ajw/articles/13520130|title=Male nurse racked by guilt at failure to save elderly residents|newspaper=The Asahi Shimbun|date=2020-07-06|accessdate=2020-07-07|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707133608/http://www.asahi.com/ajw/articles/13520130|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

彻夜的降雨过后，熊本县和[[鹿儿岛市|鹿儿岛市]]有7.5万多名居民撤离<ref name=ABCAU>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-07-04/heavy-rain-floods-southern-japan/12422720|title=Heavy rain floods southern Japan, leaving many presumed dead, several missing|date=2020-07-04|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=2020-07-10|archive-date=2020-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706074106/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-07-04/heavy-rain-floods-southern-japan/12422720|dead-url=no}}</ref>，20.3万名居民就地庇护，当地开放190家庇护中心<ref name= kyodonews>{{Cite web|url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/07/d937a4f28f92-75000-in-southwestern-japan-ordered-to-evacuate-due-to-heavy-rain.html|title=1 dead, 15 feared dead, 9 missing in rain, floods in southwest Japan|date=2020-07-04|accessdate=2020-07-08|website=Kyodo News+|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707133550/https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/07/d937a4f28f92-75000-in-southwestern-japan-ordered-to-evacuate-due-to-heavy-rain.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
